(67688, 2079, 60549, 'Salahuddin Ayubi', 997, '', 1257227491, '[quote=khakiMB]\na. Do you shoot him dead?\nb. Do you shoot him in the Leg? (If so and supposing he has a weapon he may shoot back)\nc. Do you wait and see if he has a weapon, if he does and threatens you only then you shoot him?\nd. Other (Please mention)[/quote]\n\n-> If he has entered my premises AND he has a weapon AND I am quite certain that he is a BG ===> (a). Shoot him dead\n\n-> If he has entered my premises AND I cannot see a weapon AND I am unsure he''s a BG ===> I will fire warning shots and ask him to freeze/halt. If he does not comply, will first try to shoot to injure him. Then it depends on what level of threat I perceive at that particular point of time. \n\n-> Another simplified approach is that generally houses have two gates, one is the outside gate which leads to a garage or garden, while the other is the inner gate which gives access to the house''s interior section. If the BG has not yet entered the inner cordon/perimeter, then:\n\n- shoot to injure, if he is armed;\n\n- shoot to warn, if he is apparently unarmed;\n\nwhereas, if he has entered the inner perimeter, then:\n\n- shoot to injure, if he is apparently unarmed; and\n\n- shoot to kill, if he is armed.', 0, 1, '61.5.135.53', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2736, 76461),
