(77416, 2149, 63084, 'Skeeter60', 861, '', 1260634468, '[quote=faisji]Shooting an AR15 w/ 7inch Barrel (SBR) at 530 yards!!\n\n[url]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JK2qxVXj4UU[/url][/quote]\n\nIn CQB instant killability is desired. The five five six rd from a 20 inch barrel kills primarily because of the bullet breaking up into three parts inside the target or by yawing and thus causing a large wound channel. \nAt the reduced velocities from short barrels of the M4 carbine etc these effects do not occur; this is what is causing complaints and the need for the 6.8 SPC. About the hydrostatic shock it appears no one told the Taliban or the Iraqi''s they are supposed to be shocked when shot.\nI have taken all types of game and even a 7mm Magnum shooting a 160 gr Nosler Partition at 3000 feet per second does not shock an animal when hit squarely between the shoulders, I have seen Ibex, and Urial run 20 to 50 yds before dropping. You bet if the Ibex was holding an AK he would have loosened a complete 30 shot magazine at me before going down.   \nThe 556 is now a 50 year old round and none of the armies using it has been able to discard the old 762; all platoon machine guns are 762 along with sniper rifles. And the 556 carbines and submachine guns are relatively weaker in stopping an adversary in CQB where one needs maximum lethality.', 0, 1, '119.154.67.93', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2825, 87066),
